APR stands for Annual Percentage Rate. It is the annual interest rate charged for borrowing or earned through an investment, and it represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. It includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.Say it as a poemAPR, a rate so grand,
Annual Percentage Rate, across the land.
It's the cost of borrowing, or earning, you see,
Including fees, for a year's decree.
